## ğŸ†˜ When to Use This

### Use Connection Test When:
- App won't load
- Getting database errors
- After network changes
- Troubleshooting startup issues

### Use AppSettings Validator When:
- Seeing "appName undefined" errors
- Colors not applying correctly
- Default language not working
- Any configuration-related issues

### Use Backup When:
- Before major configuration changes
- Weekly maintenance routine
- Before updating app version
- Before infrastructure changes

### Use Collections Monitor When:
- Checking data integrity
- Monitoring app usage
- Planning database optimization
- Investigating missing data

### Use Help Guide When:
- Troubleshooting problems
- Setting up for first time
- Learning best practices
- Understanding error messages

---

## ğŸ“Š What the Numbers Mean

**Status & Health Tab**:
- **Total Collections**: Number of data collections in Firebase
- **Total Documents**: Total number of records across all collections
- **Database Health**: Percentage indicator of health (0-100%)

**Collections Tab**:
- **Active**: Collection exists with documents
- **Empty**: Collection exists but has no documents
- **Missing**: Collection hasn't been created yet

